'''Abu Road railway station''' is located in [[Sirohi district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of  [[Rajasthan]] . It serves [[Abu Road]] and is gateway to the popular [[hill station]] at [[Mount Abu]].

==The railway station==
Abu Road railway station is at an elevation of {{convert|262.430|m|ft}} and is assigned the code – ABR.<ref>{{cite web|url=  http://indiarailinfo.com/arrivals/abu-road-abr/131|title= Arrivals at Abu Road|publisher= indiarailinfo| accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>

==History==
Rajputana State Railway opened the Delhi-Bandikui  {{RailGauge|1000mm}} wide [[metre gauge]] line in 1874, extended it to Ajmer in 1875 and to Ahmedabad in 1881.<ref name=irfcaii>{{cite web|url= http://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-history2.html |title= IR History: Early Days II (1870-1899)| publisher=IRFCA| accessdate=23 April 2014}}</ref> The Delhi-Ajmer metre gauge line was converted to  {{RailGauge|1676mm}} wide [[Indian gauge|broad gauge]] in 1994. The Ahmedabad-Ajmer sector was fully converted to broad gauge in 1997 – parts of it were converted earlier.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-history5.html |title= IR History: Part V (1970-1995)| publisher=IRFCA| accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>

